article.headline: E. Kentucky 56, Thomas More 38
article.story: RICHMOND, Ky. (AP) -- Adam Leonard scored 13 points and Eastern Kentucky beat Division III Thomas More 56-38 on Tuesday night. The Colonels (2-0) raced out to a 21-8 lead. The Saints rallied and narrowed the margin to four twice in the last nine minutes but couldn't get any closer. Leonard hit three of his team's 10 3-pointers. Josh Daniel had 10 points. Daniel came off the bench and scored eight of the Colonels' first 19 points. Eastern scored 15 of those points from 3-point range. Mark Tinklenberg scored all of his 17 points in the first half for the Saints, including three consecutive 3-pointers. Tinklenberg finished with five 3-pointers in the half. The Colonels led 33-26 at halftime, then hit three 3-pointers as they outscored Thomas More 13-2 to open the second half.
